A quick update:
As you all know, our community has been shocked and saddened by the death of one of our own. In the wake of such a serious tragedy, it feels wrong to post the normally inappropriate or petty secrets I usually receive. As a moment of silence of sorts, I will not be posting through the weekend, unless it is relevant to the devastation the community is currently feeling or honoring Melissa. If you were personally affected by Melissa's passing, stay strong and do not be afraid to talk to anyone. Know that the Counseling Center is always available as is the entire 'Cane family. Those of you who did not know Melissa, consider reaching out and assisting those who are going through such a tragic loss. UMiami is blessed with an incredibly strong community - never forget that. My thoughts and prayers are with Delta Phi Epsilon and Melissa's friends and families. Stay strong, 'Canes.

On that note, if anyone ever has a personal problem with a secret - PLEASE either message me or send in a submission if you want to be anonymous.  If you report a post through Facebook, I get banned from posting for at least 24 hours and potentially the page will get deleted.
There have been times when things get deleted because I realized it was in bad taste to post, or the OP asks me to take it down, or someone finds it offensive.

If you feel confident that you truly understand the material like you said, then while taking the test: 1)read the question as if there were no choices given
2)come up with what you think is the right answer without looking at the given options.
3) now look at the choices and see if your answer is also there (they usually are, if you are proficient in the material)
4) then mark that option and move on. 
5) Do not waste your time reading and considering the wrong answers, they are only there to trick you by making you doubt yourself.

data.message:
Ok, Evan, we're gonna do a little basic math here. Let's say it's an 8-ounce glass at 0 degrees C. A calorie is the energy it takes to raise 1 gram of water by 1 degree C.
8 ounces = 237 mL = 237 g
Body temp is 37 degrees, so we're raising 237 g by 37 degrees. 237 * 37 = 8,769 calories. Then times 2 for the second glass = 17,538
Converting to food Calories (or kilocalories) is 17.5 Calories. Congrats, you just burned about 5 M&Ms.
